The '''Electoral Commission of Catalonia''' ({{lang-ca|Sindicatura Electoral de Catalunya}}) was the [[electoral commission]] for the [[Catalan independence referendum, 2017|independence referendum]], guaranteeing the transparency and objectivity of the electoral process and the effective exercise of electoral rights. It is based in [[Parliament of Catalonia]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=|first1=|title=Electoral comissions|url=https://www.referendum.cat/en/electoral-comissions/|agency=Generalitat de Catalunya|date=|accessdate=12 September 2017}}</ref> On September 21, 2017, the [[Constitutional Court of Spain]] imposed daily fines of 12,000 euros for each member of the commission, and 6,000 euros for each territorial trustee.  One of the members, [[Josep Maria Jové i Lladó]] ([[:ca:Josep Maria Jové i Lladó|ca]], [[:es:Josep Maria Jové i Lladó|es]]), resigned after being arrested, to avoid the fine.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elmundo.es/cataluna/2017/09/22/59c4d9dd22601dde118b4655.html|title=El Govern disuelve la Sindicatura Electoral para no pagar la multa y fía el 1-O a observadores internacionales|work=ELMUNDO|access-date=2017-09-23|language=es}}</ref>  On September 22, 2017, the Commission dissolved itself.<ref name="Briefing #5 - 29.09.2017">{{Cite web |url=http://exteriors.gencat.cat/ca/actualitat/notes-de-context/#bloc1 |title=Notes de context - Briefing #5 - 29.09.2017 |date=2017-09-29 |website=Generalitat de Catalunya -  Departament d'Afers i Relacions Institucionals i Exteriors i Transparència}}</ref>

==Composition==
It was a permanent body made up of five members, either jurists or political scientists, experts in electoral processes, appointed by an absolute majority of the Parliament of Catalonia at the proposal of the parties, federations, coalitions or voter groupings with representation in the Parliament of Catalonia.

