The '''Tennessee Open Records Act''' is a law that states that any citizen of [[Tennessee]] may request public records there.  Public documents shall "be open for personal inspection by any citizen of Tennessee."  However, recent [[United States federal courts|federal court]] rulings have overturned similar state specific statutes and open up records in these states to all [[Citizenship in the United States|U.S. citizens]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rcfp.org/tennessee-open-government-guide |title=Tennessee |publisher=Open Government Guide |work=Reporters Committee for Freedom of the Press }}</ref>

